    <name type="primary" sortindex="1" value="Aces High: Blue Max"/>
    <description>Blue Max is not a complete game in itself; it is an expansion kit for 3W's popular game  Aces High, dealing with aerial combat during World War 1. Coverage of the Great War in the air is extended to cover Italy, Macedonia and Palestine, as well as the strategic bombing raids on Britain and Germany. Counters and data sheets are provided for 39 new types and variants of aircraft; over 20 new scenarios are provided which use these new aircraft as well as several types which were provided in the original game, but for which no scenario was given. Extra rules are provided extending the detailed coverage of the subject. The numbering of these rules has been kept. consistent with that of Aces High.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The reissued boxed version of Aces High incorporates the additional rules and planes of Aces High: Blue Max within the box. However, Aces High: Blue Max continued to be sold seperately as a stand-alone expansion.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Expands:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;    Aces High&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
